Where an identity matching process is completed, whether successfully or 
unsuccessfully, the relying party shall keep the logs relating to the identity 
matching process and its outcome, including:
(a) the values provided by the user and the relying party;
(b) the date and time of the identity matching process;
(c) any relevant documentation provided as part of complementary methods;
(d) any identifiers or account numbers used.

Relying parties shall retain the logs for a minimum of 6 months and a maximum 
of 12 months for security purposes.
